=== 審判 ===

2011年1月底，通常由醫師及心理學家所組成的陸軍精神健全委員會判定哈桑神智清楚，可以受審。<ref name="sig"/> 這就表示允許對其進行死刑案的審判程序。在審訊期間，辯方可以提出更多關於哈桑於槍擊事件時精神狀態的資訊。<ref name="sig"/>

2011年7月20日，哈桑被正式提訊。<ref>[http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/21/us/21hood.html?hp Suspect Is Arraigned in Fort Hood Massacre] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/21/us/21hood.html?hp |date=20201108212411 }}, ''[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]'', July 20, 2011. Retrieved July 20, 2011</ref> 他本人並沒有提出抗辯，於是法官准允其律師的請求於之後某一日期再提出抗辯。法官最初將哈桑少校的軍法審判日期定為2012年3月5日。<ref>{{cite web|last=Shannon|first=Kelley|title=Texas base shooting trial set for March 2012|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/20/us-usa-shooting-texas-idUSTRE76J6DU20110720|agency=Reuters|accessdate=July 22, 2012|date=July 20, 2011|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924154257/http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/20/us-usa-shooting-texas-idUSTRE76J6DU20110720|dead-url=no}}</ref> 之後，哈桑換了律師，為了使他們有時間準備為其辯護，軍法審判的日期便往後延期。<ref name="ChiTJun2012">{{cite news |title=Accused Fort Hood massacre shooter to seek another delay |author=Jim Forsyth |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-06-18/news/sns-rt-us-usa-crime-forthoodbre85h1uv-20120618_1_nidal-hasan-accused-fort-hood-shooting-spree |newspaper=Chicago Tribune |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=August 6, 2012 |archive-date=2013-05-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515053022/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-06-18/news/sns-rt-us-usa-crime-forthoodbre85h1uv-20120618_1_nidal-hasan-accused-fort-hood-shooting-spree |dead-url=no }}</ref>

先前已吩咐過哈桑遵守軍規並且剃去其所留鬍子的法官貴格里·格羅斯（Gregory Gross）上校，於2012年7月發現其蔑視命令而將其處以罰金。哈桑的軍事審判則定於2012年8月20日開庭。<ref>{{cite news |title=Judge: Fort Hood suspect could be shaved |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.armytimes.com/news/2012/07/ap-fort-hood-shooter-could-be-forcibly-shaved-072512/ |newspaper=Army Times |date=July 25, 2012 |accessdate=August 6, 2012 |archive-date=2019-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822025935/https://www.armytimes.com/news/2012/07/ap-fort-hood-shooter-could-be-forcibly-shaved-072512/ |dead-url=no }}</ref> 哈桑因保留鬍子而再次被罰，並遭警告在進行軍法審判前可以強迫其刮鬍子。<ref>{{cite news |title=Fort Hood shooting suspect fined by judge once more after again showing up in court with beard |author=Angela K. Brown |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/fort-hood-shooting-suspect-will-be-in-court-for-hearing-only-if-he-obeyed-order-to-shave-beard/2012/08/03/bebca710-dd39-11e1-8ad1-909913931f71_story.html |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=August 3, 2012 |accessdate=August 6, 2012 |archive-date=2018-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181207171009/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/fort-hood-shooting-suspect-will-be-in-court-for-hearing-only-if-he-obeyed-order-to-shave-beard/2012/08/03/bebca710-dd39-11e1-8ad1-909913931f71_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

8月15日，哈桑按預定時間，針對在軍法審判開始之前所對他的指控提出抗辯。由於控方極力尋求將此案判成[[死刑|死刑]]，哈桑於是未被獲准對蓄意謀殺的指控承認有罪。<ref>{{cite news|title=Not guilty pleas expected in Fort Hood case|author=Angela K. Brown|url=http://www.armytimes.com//news/2012/08/ap-fort-hood-pleas-expected-081512|newspaper=Army Times|date=August 15, 2012|accessdate=August 16, 2012|archive-date=2019-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822025934/https://www.armytimes.com/news/2012/08/ap-fort-hood-pleas-expected-081512/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 因哈桑反對在違背其意願下剃去鬍子，其律師便向{{Link-en|美國三軍上訴法院|United States Court of Appeals for the Armed Forces}}提出上訴。哈桑說蓄鬍是其宗教信仰的一部分。<ref>{{cite news |title=Fort Hood Suspect's Trial on Hold Over Beard |author=Angela K. Brown |url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/fort-hood-suspects-trial-hold-beard-17016993#.UCyhdKlmRNs |publisher=ABC News |date=August 16, 2012 |accessdate=August 16, 2012 |archive-date=2012-08-16 |archive-url=http://web.archive.bibalex.org/web/20120816170336/http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/fort-hood-suspects-trial-hold-beard-17016993#.UCyhdKlmRNs |dead-url=no }}</ref>

8月27日，上訴法院宣布，審判可以繼續，但並未裁決是否可以強迫哈桑刮鬍子。上訴法院已經駁回了哈桑之前的請求以「宗教通融」為由免受軍規以保留鬍子。<ref>{{cite news|title=Military says trial of accused Fort Hood shooter can go ahead|author=Karen Brooks|editor-first=Greg|editor-last=McCune|editor2-first=Todd|editor2-last=Eastham|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/sns-rt-us-usa-crime-forthoodbre87q176-20120827,0,1757940.story|agency=Reuters|newspaper=Chicago Tribune|date=August 27, 2012|accessdate=August 27, 2012}}{{Dead link|date=2019年5月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> 9月6日，在法院裁定1993年的《{{Link-en|宗教自由恢復法案|Religious Freedom Restoration Act}}》不適用於本案後，格羅斯便下令要哈桑剃去鬍子。儘管如此，直到哈桑的上訴用盡之前，都不能予以強制執行，也因此進一步地拖延了審判。<ref>{{cite news|title=Fort Hood Shooting Suspect’s Beard Must Be Shaved, Military Judge Rules|author=Manny Ramirez|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/09/07/us/judge-in-fort-hood-case-orders-maj-nidal-malik-hasans-beard-shaved.html?_r=0|newspaper=San Francs|date=September 6, 2012|accessdate=September 17, 2012|archive-date=2020-11-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107165225/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/09/07/us/judge-in-fort-hood-case-orders-maj-nidal-malik-hasans-beard-shaved.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="AKB6SEP12AP">{{cite news|title=Hasan ordered shaved; trial delayed|author=Angela K. Brown|url=http://www.statesman.com/news/local/hasan-ordered-shaved-trial-delayed-2452386.html|agency=Associated Press|newspaper=Austin Statesmen|date=September 6, 2012|accessdate=September 17, 2012}}{{Dead link|date=2018年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

2012年9月6日，在庭訊期間，哈桑兩次試圖認罪。然而，陸軍軍規禁止法官在死刑案中接受認罪。<ref name="AKB6SEP12AP" /> 9月21日，哈桑的辯護律師就哈桑的鬍子向{{Link-en|美國陸軍刑事上訴法院|United States Army Court of Criminal Appeals|陸軍刑事上訴法院}}提出兩件上訴，審判因而延期。<ref>{{cite news|title=Nidal Hasan, Fort Hood Suspect, Appeals Beard Shaving Order|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/21/fort-hood-suspect-appeals_0_n_1904899.html|work=Huffington Post|agency=Associated Press|date=September 21, 2012|accessdate=October 2, 2012|archive-date=2016-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308195311/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/21/fort-hood-suspect-appeals_0_n_1904899.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 基林市民則對延期受審感到相當沮喪。<ref>{{cite news|title=Killeen residents angry with delays in Hasan trial|author=Chris Cheng|url=http://www.kxxv.com/story/19610597/killeen-residents-angry-with-delays-in-hasan-trial|publisher=KXXV|date=September 21, 2012|accessdate=October 2, 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004213217/http://www.kxxv.com/story/19610597/killeen-residents-angry-with-delays-in-hasan-trial|archive-date=2013-10-04|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

10月中旬，陸軍刑事上訴法院維持格羅斯上校的判決，可以強迫哈桑刮鬍子。<ref>{{cite news |title=Army appeals court rules Fort Hood shooting suspect can be forcibly shaved before trial |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/army-appeals-court-rules-fort-hood-shooting-suspect-can-be-forcibly-shaved-before-trial/2012/10/18/1eaea63a-1973-11e2-ad4a-e5a958b60a1e_story.html |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=October 18, 2012 |accessdate=October 23, 2012 |archive-date=2018-12-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181225150023/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/army-appeals-court-rules-fort-hood-shooting-suspect-can-be-forcibly-shaved-before-trial/2012/10/18/1eaea63a-1973-11e2-ad4a-e5a958b60a1e_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 哈桑的律師則向三軍上訴法院提出上訴，以企圖推翻下級法院的裁決並將格羅斯撤換。<ref>{{cite news |title=Hood suspect appeals forcible-shaving ruling |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.militarytimes.com/news/2012/11/ap-hood-suspect-hasan-appeals-forcible-shaving-ruling-110812/ |newspaper=Military Times |date=November 8, 2012 |accessdate=November 13, 2012 |archive-date=2020-11-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201124001448/https://www.militarytimes.com/news/2012/11/ap-hood-suspect-hasan-appeals-forcible-shaving-ruling-110812/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2012年12月4日（週二），三軍上訴法院取消了哈桑少校蔑視法庭的六項定罪，並將法官格羅斯上校從本案撤去，同時聲明格羅斯沒有表現出必要的公正性。該上訴法院也推翻了強迫哈桑刮鬍子的命令，但沒有對哈桑的宗教權利是否受到侵犯作出裁決。<ref>{{cite news |title=Fort Hood Nidal Hasan shooting trial judge removed |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-20589733 |newspaper=BBC News |date=December 3, 2012 |accessdate=December 4, 2012 |archive-date=2019-04-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190417144659/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-20589733 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fort Hood shooting judge removed for showing bias|agency=Associated Press|url=http://www.pjstar.com/free/x2105846060/Fort-Hood-shooting-judge-removed-for-showing-bias|newspaper=[[Peoria_Journal_Star|Peoria Journal Star]]|publisher=GateHouse Media, Inc.|date=December 3, 2012|accessdate=December 4, 2012|archive-date=2013-10-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004220103/http://www.pjstar.com/free/x2105846060/Fort-Hood-shooting-judge-removed-for-showing-bias|dead-url=no}}</ref> 此外，該上訴法院也裁示，確保哈桑符合儀容標準是軍事指揮官的職責，而非軍事法庭法官。<ref>{{cite news|title=Suspect in Ft. Hood shootings can keep his beard – for now|author=Matt Pearce|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-na-hasan-judge-20121204,0,4626692.story|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|date=December 3, 2012|accessdate=December 4, 2012|archive-date=2019-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822025936/https://www.latimes.com/world/la-xpm-2012-dec-03-la-na-hasan-judge-20121204-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{Link-en|美國陸軍軍法局長|Judge Advocate General of the United States Army|陸軍軍法局長}}於是任命了一名新法官來取代格羅斯。<ref name="SAEN4DEC12">{{cite news |title=Judge in Hasan case removed |author=Sig Christenson |url=http://www.mysanantonio.com/news/military/article/Appeals-court-removes-Hasan-s-judge-4088039.php |newspaper=San Antonio Express-News |date=December 4, 2012 |accessdate=December 4, 2012 |archive-date=2017-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170927221137/http://www.mysanantonio.com/news/military/article/Appeals-court-removes-Hasan-s-judge-4088039.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>{{Link-en|聖瑪麗大學|St. Mary's University, Texas}}恐怖主義法中心主任傑佛瑞·艾迪卡特（Jeffrey Addicott）稱此為「不尋常」的裁決，而軍事法庭辯護律師法蘭克·斯賓納（Frank Spinner）則稱其為「罕見」。<ref name="SAEN4DEC12" />

陸軍上校塔拉·奧斯本（Tara A. Osborn）在格羅斯被撤換的當天被任命為本案的新任法官。<ref>{{cite news |title=Texas: New Judge in Fort Hood Shooting Case |author=Manny Fernandez |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/05/us/texas-new-judge-in-fort-hood-shooting-case.html |newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |date=December 4, 2012 |accessdate=December 11, 2012 |archive-date=2018-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618102509/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/05/us/texas-new-judge-in-fort-hood-shooting-case.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 2011年，奧斯本曾主審中士約瑟夫·伯日柯維奇（Joseph Bozicevich）的死刑案，該中士因殺害其[[班長|班長]]及另一名士兵而被判[[無期徒刑|無期徒刑]]且無假釋的可能，但得以免去死刑。<ref>{{cite news|title=New judge appointed in Fort Hood shooting case|agency=Associated Press|url=http://www.armytimes.com/news/2012/12/ap-new-judge-appointed-fort-hood-shooting-case-120412|newspaper=ArmyTimes|date=December 4, 2012|accessdate=December 11, 2012|archive-date=2019-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822025935/https://www.armytimes.com/news/2012/12/ap-new-judge-appointed-fort-hood-shooting-case-120412/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2013年1月，當哈桑被判將面臨死刑時，由於辯護律師聲稱陸軍中將{{Link-en|唐納德·坎貝爾|Donald M. Campbell, Jr.|坎貝爾}}有失公允，奧斯本正考慮是否因此免去死刑。<ref>{{cite news|title=Hasan faces death penalty|author=Sig Christenson|url=http://www.mysanantonio.com/news/military/article/Hasan-faces-death-penalty-1454855.php|newspaper=San Antonio Express News|date=July 7, 2011|accessdate=January 26, 2013|archive-date=2020-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122061457/https://www.mysanantonio.com/news/military/article/Hasan-faces-death-penalty-1454855.php|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Hood shooting suspect wants death penalty out|author=Angela K. Brown |agency=Associated Press|url=http://www.armytimes.com/mobile/news/2013/01/ap-hood-shooting-suspect-death-penalty-out-hasan-012413|newspaper=Army Times |date=January 24, 2013 |accessdate=January 26, 2013}}</ref> 1月31日，奧斯本裁定，基於1996年最高法院關於{{Link-en|德懷特·拉文|Dwight J. Loving}}的案例，死刑謀殺罪的審理程序是符合憲法的。她同時也裁決，對於哈桑的鬍子，她的法庭沒有審判權，也沒有職權命令或阻止哈桑的指揮鏈去剃他的鬍子。<ref>{{cite news |title=Death penalty still a possibility for Hasan |author=Philip Jankowski |url=http://kdhnews.com/news/death-penalty-still-a-possibility-for-hasan/article_40957a18-6b66-11e2-bca3-0019bb30f31a.html |newspaper=Killeen Daily Herald |date=January 31, 2013 |accessdate=February 12, 2013 |archive-date=2020-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123001807/https://kdhnews.com/news/death-penalty-still-a-possibility-for-hasan/article_40957a18-6b66-11e2-bca3-0019bb30f31a.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 截至2013年2月28日，軍法審判定於2013年5月29日開始，陪審員選任程序則定於2013年7月1日開始。<ref>{{cite news |title=Fort Hood shooting trial set for May 29 |author=Angela K. Brown |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.armytimes.com/mobile/news/2013/02/ap-fort-hood-shooting-trial-set-may-29-022813 |newspaper=Army Times |date=February 28, 2013 |accessdate=March 5, 2013 |archive-date=2019-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822025935/https://www.armytimes.com/mobile/news/2013/02/ap-fort-hood-shooting-trial-set-may-29-022813/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2013年6月3日，軍事法庭法官批准哈桑可以在即將要來的謀殺罪審訊中為自己辯護。他的律師團仍將繼續留在本案中，但也只有當哈桑要求協助時才可。陪審員選任程序於6月5日開始，開放辯論則於8月6日舉行。<ref>{{cite web|title=Fort Hood accused Hasan 'can represent himself'|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-22760465|publisher=BBC|accessdate=3 June 2013|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112021510/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-22760465|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Forsyth|first=Jim|title=udge rules Fort Hood suspect can represent himself|url=http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/06/03/18726775-judge-rules-fort-hood-suspect-can-represent-himself?lite|work=Reuters|publisher=NBCNews|accessdate=16 June 2013|date=3 June 2013|archive-date=2017-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928005533/http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/06/03/18726775-judge-rules-fort-hood-suspect-can-represent-himself?lite|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2013年6月14日，奧斯本裁定，哈桑不能聲稱自己是在護衛塔利班以作為自己的部分辯護。<ref>{{cite news|last=Johnson|first=M. Alex|title=Fort Hood gunman Nidal Hasan banned from arguing he was defending the Taliban|url=http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/06/14/18960053-fort-hood-gunman-nidal-hasan-banned-from-arguing-he-was-defending-the-taliban|accessdate=16 June 2013|newspaper=NBCNews|date=14 June 2013|archive-date=2019-09-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190909042847/http://usnews.nbcnews.com/_news/2013/06/14/18960053-fort-hood-gunman-nidal-hasan-banned-from-arguing-he-was-defending-the-taliban|dead-url=no}}</ref> 此外，軍審則改定於8月6日開始。<ref name="Daily Mail 27 June">{{cite news|last=|first=|title=Fort Hood shooter accused of killing 13 and wounding 32 speaks out ahead of trial to claim America has a 'war against Islam'|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2380077/Major-Nidal-Hasan-Fort-Hood-shooter-accused-killing-13-wounding-32-speaks-ahead-trial-claim-America-war-Islam.html#ixzz2aKHWJlpw|accessdate=28 July 2013|newspaper=Daily Mail|date=27 July 2013|archive-date=2020-12-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201213201117/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2380077/Major-Nidal-Hasan-Fort-Hood-shooter-accused-killing-13-wounding-32-speaks-ahead-trial-claim-America-war-Islam.html#ixzz2aKHWJlpw|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在一次[[福斯新聞頻道|福斯新聞]]的獨家專訪中，哈桑聲稱美軍那時正與伊斯蘭交戰，藉此為自己在胡德堡槍擊事件中的行為辯護。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Herridge|first1=Catherine|last2=Browne|first2=Pamela|title=Accused Fort Hood shooter releases statement to Fox News|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2013/07/26/accused-fort-hood-shooter-claims-us-military-at-war-with-his-religion/#ixzz2aKLkSjzr|accessdate=28 July 2013|agency=Fox News|date=26 July 2013|archive-date=2015-10-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151014220708/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2013/07/26/accused-fort-hood-shooter-claims-us-military-at-war-with-his-religion/#ixzz2aKLkSjzr|dead-url=no}}</ref> 這次訪談是自哈桑被捕以來，首次與美國媒體進行談話。在過去，哈桑只經由電話與半島電視台交談。<ref name="Daily Mail 27 June" />

8月6日，軍法審判首日，自我辯護的哈桑承認，他就是2009年胡德堡槍擊案中的持槍歹徒，並陳述證據清楚顯示他就是槍手。他還告訴陪審團他已「轉為敵方」，並將自己視為一名對美國進行聖戰的聖戰士。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Allen|first1=Nick|title=I am the shooter: US army major Nidal Hasan declares as he faces court martial over Fort Hood massacre|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/10226875/I-am-the-shooter-US-army-major-Nidal-Hasan-declares-as-he-faces-court-martial-over-Fort-Hood-massacre.html|accessdate=8 August 2013|agency=The Telegraph (UK)|date=6 August 2013|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128114513/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/10226875/I-am-the-shooter-US-army-major-Nidal-Hasan-declares-as-he-faces-court-martial-over-Fort-Hood-massacre.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 8月7日，哈桑與其辯護律師團間的分歧致使奧斯本法官不得不暫緩訴訟進程。哈桑的辯護律師擔心，哈桑自己的辯護策略會使自己遭判死刑。由於檢方求處死刑，其辯護律師團已經試圖阻止。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Merchant|first1=Nomaan|last2=Weber|first2=Paul|title=Nidal Hasan Cross-Examination: Fort Hood Shooting Suspect Asks No Questions Of First Victim|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/07/nidal-hasan-cross-examination_n_3718398.html|accessdate=8 August 2013|agency=The Huffington Post|date=8 August 2013|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304080905/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/07/nidal-hasan-cross-examination_n_3718398.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 定罪 ===

2013年8月23日，在陪審團仔細考慮了7個小時後，哈桑在所有指控中被判有罪。<ref>{{cite web|last=Carter|first=Chelsea J. Carter|title=Nidal Hasan convicted in Fort Hood shootings; jurors can decide death|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/08/23/justice/nidal-hasan-court-martial-friday/index.html|publisher=CNN|accessdate=24 August 2013|date=23 August 2013|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206234928/https://edition.cnn.com/2013/08/23/justice/nidal-hasan-court-martial-friday/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 宣判 ===

2013年8月28日，美國軍事法庭就此槍擊案判處哈桑死刑。就在判決宣布之時，哈桑成了軍中僅有的6名死刑犯之一。<ref>{{cite news|title=Fort Hood shooter Nidal Hasan sentenced to death|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/story/2013/08/28/us-ft-hood-massacre-death-sentence-nidal-hasan.html?cmp=rss|accessdate=31 August 2013|agency=CBC|date=28 August 2013|archive-date=2013-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130904174311/http://www.cbc.ca/news/world/story/2013/08/28/us-ft-hood-massacre-death-sentence-nidal-hasan.html?cmp=rss|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 內部調查 ===

{{Main|聯合反恐任務小組}}

聯邦調查局指出，早在2008年12月，哈桑就受到{{Link-en|聯合反恐任務小組|Joint Terrorism Task Force}}（JTTF）的注意。哈桑與奧拉基間的往來通信，以及其他相似的通訊，都經過審查，且被認為與他在沃爾特·里德醫療中心所作的專業研究相符。聯調局表示：「由於通信的內容都可由其所作的研究來解釋，且無發現其他貶損之事，聯合反恐任務小組於是推斷，哈桑少校沒有涉及任何恐怖行動或恐怖策劃。」<ref name="NYT 13" />

2009年12月，聯邦調查局長[[羅伯特·米勒|羅伯特·米勒]]任命前局長{{Link-en|威廉·韋伯斯特|William H. Webster}}設立一個委員會，以對聯調局在評估哈桑所造成之風險的處理上進行獨立審查。<ref name="Webster" />

2010年1月15日，國防部發布其調查結果，發現國防部自身對於防範內部的威脅毫無準備。部長[[羅伯特·蓋茨|羅伯特·蓋茨]]說，以往的事件並未使軍中的職場暴力及「自我激化」獲得足夠的關注。他也指出，在槍擊案發生前，沒能對哈桑加以注意，有些軍官應對此負有責任。<ref>{{Cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/16/us/politics/16hasan.html | title=Pentagon Report on Fort Hood Details Failures | work=The New York Times | date=January 15, 2010 | first1=Elisabeth | last1=Bumiller | first2=Scott | last2=Shane | accessdate=May 2, 2010 | archive-date=2020-12-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218115523/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/01/16/us/politics/16hasan.html | dead-url=no }}</ref> 國防部的這份報告並未提及哈桑的動機。<ref name=timejan20/>

一名陸軍後備役中校且是愛沙尼亞{{Link-en|波羅的海國防學院|Baltic Defence College}}的{{Link-en|詹姆斯·克朗姆|James Corum}}，稱國防部的這份報告為「曲解不實」，因該份報告竟沒提到哈桑對伊斯蘭教有多虔誠及其如何變得激進。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Corum|first=James|url=http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/jamescorum/100023177/pentagon-report-on-fort-hood-is-a-travesty-that-doesnt-even-mention-islam/|title=Pentagon report on Fort Hood is a travesty that doesn't even mention Islam – Telegraph Blogs|work=The Daily Telegraph|date=January 21, 2010|accessdate=February 5, 2010|location=London|archive-date=2016-03-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303184047/http://blogs.telegraph.co.uk/news/jamescorum/100023177/pentagon-report-on-fort-hood-is-a-travesty-that-doesnt-even-mention-islam/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 德州眾議員[[約翰·卡特|約翰·卡特]]也批評該報告並說，他覺得政府是「害怕被指控將某人描繪成罪犯」。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2010/01/19/gop-congressman-blasts-pentagon-report-fort-hood-shooting/?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%253A+foxnews%252Fpolitics+%2528Text+-+Politics%2529|title=GOP Congressman Blasts Pentagon Report on Fort Hood Shooting|publisher=Fox News|date=January 19, 2010|accessdate=February 5, 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009123032/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2010/01/19/gop-congressman-blasts-pentagon-report-fort-hood-shooting/?utm_source=feedburner&utm_medium=feed&utm_campaign=Feed%3A+foxnews%2Fpolitics+%28Text+-+Politics%29|archive-date=2013-10-09|dead-url=yes}}</ref>{{Link-en|九一一委員會|9/11 Commission|911委員會}}的成員同時也是[[罗纳德·里根|雷根]]時代的[[美國海軍部長|海軍部長]]{{Link-en|約翰·萊曼|John F. Lehman}}說，他認為該份報告是「讓你看見[[政治正確|政治正確]]的價值觀已經變得有多麼根深蒂固。」<ref name=timejan20>{{Cite news|last=Thompson|first=Mark|url=http://www.time.com/time/nation/article/0,8599,1954960,00.html|title=Fort Hood Report: No Mention of Islam, Hasan Not Named|work=Time|date=January 20, 2010|accessdate=February 5, 2010|archive-date=2013-08-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130817075216/http://www.time.com/time/nation/article/0,8599,1954960,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[舊金山紀事報|舊金山紀事報]]》的專欄作家{{Link-en|黛布拉·桑德|Debra Saunders}}在一則評論中寫道：「……若該份報告的目的是要將所獲得的教訓精心編製，以防止未來的攻擊發生，那他們怎麼能略去激進的伊斯蘭教而不提呢?」<ref>Saunders, Debra J., (January 25, 2010).[http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2010/01/25/EDV91BN8CP.DTL "Political correctness on Fort Hood at Pentagon"], ''San Francisco Chronicle,'' January 25, 2010</ref>

帶頭進行調查的前[[美国陆军部长|陸軍部長]]{{Link-en|多哥·韋斯特|Togo D. West, Jr.}}以及退役的海軍上將弗農·克拉克（Vernon Clark）對此回應說，他們「關注的是行動及影響，不見得是動機」，而且他們不想與目前正在對哈桑所進行的刑事調查相衝突。<ref name=timejan20/>

2010年2月，《[[波士頓環球報|波士頓環球報]]》獲得了一份機密的內部報告，當中詳述了陸軍調查的結果。根據該報報導，該份內部報告推斷，自2005年起，陸軍內部的官員便已察覺哈桑有激進的伊斯蘭傾向。當中還提到2007年的一個事件，當時哈桑在課堂上作簡報，標題為「反恐戰爭就是對伊斯蘭教的戰爭嗎？一名伊斯蘭教徒的觀點」。根據該報報導，據聞課堂講師打斷了哈桑，因為他認為這名精神科醫師正試著為恐怖主義辯護。哈桑的上級長官對這起事件並沒有採取相關的任何行動，反而相信哈桑的評論受到[[美國憲法第一修正案|美國憲法第一修正案]]的保護，並且相信有一位穆斯林的精神科醫師能促進軍中的多元化。該份報告指出，哈桑的言論或能作為將他免去職務的理由，因憲法第一修正案並不像對平民般也適用於軍人。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boston.com/news/nation/washington/articles/2010/02/22/ft_hood_suspect_was_army_dilemma/|title=Ft. Hood suspect was Army dilemma|last=Bender|first=Brian|work=Boston Globe|accessdate=February 23, 2010|date=February 22, 2010|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305005721/http://www.boston.com/news/nation/washington/articles/2010/02/22/ft_hood_suspect_was_army_dilemma/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年7月，韋伯斯特的委員會提交了最終報告。<ref name=WebsterCommissionReport>Webster Commission. July 19, 2012.[http://www.fbi.gov/news/pressrel/press-releases/final-report-of-the-william-h.-webster-commission Final Report of the William H. Webster Commission one the Federal Bureau of Investigation, Counterterrorism Intelligence, and the Events at Fort Hood, Texas, on November 5, 2009] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fbi.gov/news/pressrel/press-releases/final-report-of-the-william-h.-webster-commission |date=20131128192526 }}</ref><ref>William H Webster. July 19, 2012 [http://www.fbi.gov/news/pressrel/press-releases/william-h.-webster-commission-letter Report Transmission Letter] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fbi.gov/news/pressrel/press-releases/william-h.-webster-commission-letter |date=20131005042340 }}</ref> 韋伯斯特向聯邦調查局提出了18項建議。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fbi.gov/news/pressrel/press-releases/judge-webster-delivers-webster-commission-report-on-fort-hood|title=Judge Webster Delivers Webster Commission Report on Fort Hood|author=FBI National Press Office|date=July 19, 2012|work=Federal Bureau of Investigation|publisher=United States Department of Justice|accessdate=August 6, 2012|archive-date=2016-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129153924/https://www.fbi.gov/news/pressrel/press-releases/judge-webster-delivers-webster-commission-report-on-fort-hood|dead-url=no}}</ref> 這份報告發現在許多方面存在問題，包括資訊共享、未能跟進線索、電腦技術問題、以及聯調局總部未能協調兩間外地辦事處處理有關哈桑的線索。<ref>{{cite news |title=FBI official: Hasan should have been asked about e-mails with radical cleric |author=Carol Cratty |url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/08/01/politics/hasan-fbi/index.html |publisher=CNN |date=August 2, 2012 |accessdate=August 6, 2012 |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129014656/https://www.cnn.com/2012/08/01/politics/hasan-fbi/index.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

2013年8月，《[[瓊斯媽媽|瓊斯媽媽]]》雜誌描述了多封哈桑寄給奧拉基但遭到攔截的電郵。在一封2008年的郵件中，哈桑問奧拉基，他是否把那些死於攻擊軍中同袍的人視為「烈士」。在一封2009年的郵件中，哈桑問奧拉基，「隨意地殺害平民」是否是可以的。這兩封郵件都被轉寄到國防刑事調查局（DCIS）。然而，DCIS卻未能將此兩封郵件彼此聯繫在一起，而且只對2008年的郵件作粗略調查。一名DCIS的探員之後解釋說因郵件主旨屬於「政治敏感」。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.motherjones.com/politics/2013/08/nidal-hasan-anwar-awlaki-emails-fbi-fort-hood|title=Internal Documents Reveal How the FBI Blew Fort Hood|last=Blake|first=Mariah|accessdate=2013-10-01|archive-date=2020-12-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201218151435/https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2013/08/nidal-hasan-anwar-awlaki-emails-fbi-fort-hood/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 訴訟 ==

2011年11月，受害者及其家屬提起訴訟，宣稱政府未能在攻擊前對哈桑採取行動，是因受到「[[政治正確|政治正確]]」的左右而存心忽視。這83名原告於是向陸軍索賠7.5億美元。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/apnewsbreak-83-victims-family-members-seek-750m-for-preventable-fort-hood-tragedy/2011/11/10/gIQALoqL9M_story.html|author=AP|title=83 Victims and Family Members Seek $750 Million for Preventable Fort Hood Tragedy|work=Washington Post | deadurl=yes}} {{Dead link|date=2011年12月 |bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref>

及至2012年，國防部將這起案件歸類為一件職場暴力事件。國防部發言人說：

<blockquote>
「國防部致力於維護對少校尼達爾·哈桑所進行之軍審程序的完整性，也因此在此刻，不會對2009年11月5日在胡德堡所發生的事件作進一步的描述。哈桑少校已被指控犯有13項蓄意謀殺以及32項謀殺未遂。如同所有軍法未決之事項，被告在被證明有罪之前是無罪的。」<ref name=benghazi/>
</blockquote>

由160名受害者及其家屬所組成的團體已要求政府宣稱胡德堡的攻擊事件為恐怖行動。如此，受害者在事件中受傷可被視作為如同在戰區受傷而獲得更多福利。<ref name=benghazi />美國眾議員[[約翰·卡特|約翰·卡特]]及[[麥可·麥克考爾|麥可·麥克考爾]]從他們對現行的調查所作的解釋中，得出結論並寫道：「基於所有的事實，儘管所有的證據都在在清楚表明，胡德堡槍擊案是一件恐怖行動，國防部及陸軍卻仍持續將此攻擊列為『職場暴力』，這對我們來說實在難以想像。」<ref name=benghazi />

